title: Edgar Degas Spanish Dance Sculpture
description:
Sculpture developed from Edgar Degas’ Spanish Dancer, modeled c. 1883 (cast 1919/21) from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

A portrayal of strength, grace and elegance; this iron sculpture captures beauty in one pose.  Manufactured using the "lost wax" method.  All iron pieces are cast from a wax model.

  • Dimensions: 16.25 x 7.5 x 5 in.
  • Materials: Iron sculpture with velveteen lining to protect furniture
  • Weight: 5 lb.
  • Gently clean with cloth. 

Additional Shipping $15 per Order.

This item cannot be shipped to a destination outside the United States.
